danfulea.math

Class Matrix

  • java.lang.Object
    • danfulea.math.Matrix

  • public class Matrix
extends java.lang.Object
    Utility class for matrix operations. Based on code written by Bryan Lewis freely available on the web
    Author:
    Dan Fulea, 29 MAR. 2004

      • divide

        public static Matrix divide(Matrix m1,
                            Matrix m2)
        Matrix division m1/m2. If m2 is a 1x1 matrix, then this is just matrix/scalar. If m2 is a square, invertible matrix and m1 is a vector (a matrix with one column), divide returns inverse(m2)*m1, using the Householder QR algorithm.
        Parameters:
        m1 - 1st matrix
        m2 - 2nd matrix
        Returns:
        the matrix result

        public java.util.Vector<Matrix> qr()
        Returns:

      • toHess

        public java.util.Vector<Matrix> toHess()
        Makes the matrix upper Hessenberg via Householder reflections
        Returns:
        {P, H} s.t. P' * this * P = H and H is upper Hessenberg and P' * P = I.

      • gepp

        public java.util.Vector<Matrix> gepp()
        Returns:
        the LU decomposition of a matrix using the Gauss transform. This algorithm returns 3 matrices as follows: {P, L, U} such that LU = PA. This algorithm performs partial pivoting.

      • leig

        public double leig(double p)
        Elementary QR method method to find the spectral radius of a positive valued matrix. Parameter p = precision desired. For example, if A is a Matrix of positive real numbers, then A.leig(0.01) returns the largest eigenvalue to at least two digits of accuracy.
        Parameters:
        p - precision
        Returns:
        the largest eigenvalue

      • sort

        public Matrix sort()
        Sort this object in the following way: 1. If this is a column or row vector, sort the vector and return a two column Matrix containing the sorted vector in the first column, and the permutation indices in the 2nd column. 2. If this is a rectangular Matrix, sort the rows according to the entries in the first column.
        Returns:
        the new matrix

      • order

        public Matrix order()
        Sorts this vector, returning a ranked vector, (here, 'vector' indicates a 1-d Matrix, not the Java class Vector). 'order' is used so as to not confuse with the usual definition of rank
        Returns:
        the ranked vector
